     First,  I would like to say, sorry to see you go and that you will be missed.  Hopefully you will rethink your decision and come back.  Everyone gets frustrated sometimes and it is understandable.  <br>
     <br>
     Second,  I was there on this DN raid.  HoS givin up on the killing of the rat who had the willsapper had nothing to do with us having to do a CR.  It had everything to do with simple courtesy for another guild.  &quot;Usque Spidera&quot; got the peeps there to do the takedown before we did.  They were in the tunnel first.  Should we have rushed past them down the tunnel and tried to attack the mob first.  IMO, no.  The reason we even went deeper into the zone was to be there in case they failed, which they didnt.  Alot of us stayed even though we didnt know if we had enough to take the rat down.  We didnt leave until AFTER he was killed.  Of the 2 people who I saw that left, they both left due to RL issues.  Someone had to catch a plane, I cant remember what the other person had to do or if they offered an explanation.  But that is besides the point.  &quot;Sometimes&quot; RL issues take precidence of EQ, hehe.  I know I'm always willing to get myself kilt killin a mob and I'm under the impression that all other HoS member are willing to do the same.  In fact,  I came running from a good village group in Velks just hearing the prospect that we might be killing this Rat in DN for Sum_lucky_tank_001 or die trying....  Maybe I didnt get all the facts straight, but this was my impression of the whole event.  Feel free to tell me I am wrong.<br>
<br>
